whole of 
<collectingCountry box="[314,416,1426,1450]" name="Tanzania" pageId="9" pageNumber="874">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
, in forest and savanna, including semi-arid regions, from sea level to 
<quantity box="[197,288,1461,1485]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="874" unit="m" value="2000.0">
<elevation box="[197,288,1461,1485]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="874" unit="m" value="2000.0">2000 m</elevation>
</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kielland J" box="[308,468,1461,1485]" pageId="9" pageNumber="874" refId="ref22372" refString="Kielland J. 1990. Butterflies of Tanzania. Melbourne: Hill House." type="book" year="1990">Kielland 1990</bibRefCitation>
, p. 77, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1908" box="[605,795,1461,1485]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melanitis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="874" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="leda" subSpecies="africana">
<emphasis box="[605,795,1461,1485]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="874">M. leda africana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
)
</materialsCitation>
. Although this species varies considerably not only in coloration (most notably the underside) but also in forewing shape, it is unmistakeable in the local fauna. 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2832026354" country="Tanzania" elevation="2000" location="Not" pageId="9" pageNumber="874" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Kilimanjaro">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03E687FCFFA9FF8949ABFB53FB99FF78:8E906031FFA9FF8A4A99FA19FD78F9A3" box="[669,710,1530,1554]" country="Tanzania" name="Not" pageId="9" pageNumber="874" stateProvince="Kilimanjaro">Not</location>
encountered on 
<collectingRegion box="[907,1033,1530,1554]" country="Tanzania" name="Kilimanjaro" pageId="9" pageNumber="874">Kilimanjaro</collectingRegion>
at 
<quantity box="[1070,1155,1530,1554]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="874" unit="m" value="2000.0">
<elevation box="[1070,1155,1530,1554]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="874" unit="m" value="2000.0">2000 m</elevation>
</quantity>
or above by 
<bibRefCitation author="Liseki SD" box="[308,450,1565,1589]" pageId="9" pageNumber="874" refId="ref22668" refString="Liseki SD 2009. Butterfly diversity and its relevance to conservation in north-eastern Tanzania [PhD thesis]. Canterbury (UK): University of Kent." type="book" year="2009">Liseki (2009)</bibRefCitation>
</materialsCitation>
. 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2832026355" country="Tanzania" location="Moshi" pageId="9" pageNumber="874" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Kilimanjaro">
On the basis of two specimens from 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03E687FCFFA9FF8949ABFB53FB99FF78:8E906031FFA9FF8A4B7FF9FEFC7FF984" box="[891,961,1565,1589]" country="Tanzania" name="Moshi" pageId="9" pageNumber="874" stateProvince="Kilimanjaro">Moshi</location>
