in 
<collectionCode box="[703,777,1599,1623]" pageId="9" pageNumber="874">BMNH</collectionCode>
, and one male and three females from Taveta, c
</materialsCitation>
. 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2832026331" collectionCode="OUMNH" country="Tanzania" elevation="762" pageId="9" pageNumber="874" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Kilimanjaro">
<quantity box="[341,424,1634,1658]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="9" pageNumber="874" unit="ft" value="2500.0">
<elevation box="[341,424,1634,1658]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="9" pageNumber="874" unit="ft" value="2500.0">2500 ft</elevation>
</quantity>
(
<collectionCode box="[439,537,1634,1658]" pageId="9" pageNumber="874">OUMNH</collectionCode>
), we include this butterfly as a member of the lower slopes fauna
</materialsCitation>
. However, it is possible that it does occur within the lowest levels of the protected forest, its crepuscular habits often making it difficult to detect. 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2832026358" country="Tanzania" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="875" location="Afrotropical region" pageId="9" pageNumber="874" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Kilimanjaro">
